    {
      "type": "teach",
      "title": "Reading whole words",
      "body": "Now for the fun part — blending letters into words. Shavian is read strictly left to right, sound by sound, with no silent letters to trip you up. Look at 𐑛𐑪𐑑: 𐑛 (d) + 𐑪 (o) + 𐑑 (t) blends smoothly into \"dot\"."
    },
    {
      "type": "teach",
      "title": "Why this alphabet exists",
      "body": "George Bernard Shaw thought English spelling wasted years of every child's life learning exceptions that taught nothing about how words actually sound. His will paid for a replacement — and blending 𐑛𐑪𐑑 straight into “dot”, no guessing required, is exactly the fix he had in mind."
    },
    {
